exercise.p:
Check the presentation for errors. If you find one, circle it and describe the mistake in words. 

	\begin{aligned}
		-x + 5 \amp = -y + 3 + 5 \amp \eqnspacer \amp \text{Substitute $x = y + 3$} \\
		\amp = -y + 8 \amp \amp \text{Arithmetic} 
	\end{aligned}

Check the presentation for errors. If you find one, circle it and describe the mistake in words. 

	\begin{aligned}
	-3p + 4q \amp = 5 \\
	-3(q - 4) + 4q \amp = 5 \amp \eqnspacer \amp \text{Substitute $p = q - 4$} \\
	-3q - 12 + 4q \amp = 5 \amp \amp \text{Distributive property} \\
	q - 12 \amp = 5 \amp \amp \text{Combine like terms} \\
	q \amp = 17 \amp \amp \text{Add 12 to both sides} 
	\end{aligned}

Check the presentation for errors. If you find one, circle it and describe the mistake in words. 

	\begin{aligned}
		5x - y \amp = 4 \\
		5x - (3x + 4) \amp = 4 \amp \eqnspacer \amp \text{Substitute $y = 3x - 2$} \\
		5x - 3x - 4 \amp = 4 \amp \amp \text{Distributive property} \\
		2x - 4 \amp = 4 \amp \amp \text{Combine like terms} \\
		2x \amp = 0 \amp \amp \text{Subtract $4$ from both sides} \\
		x \amp = 0 \amp \amp \text{Divide both sides by $2$} 
	\end{aligned}
